canonical:
  title: 謝表
  author: 李仁老
  language: lzh
  text: 內宣詔命外暢威靈恩實出於非常涕難禁於增感伏念臣猥將蕞品介在荒隅早襲箕封謬傳家而負荷忽遭丹寇擅入京以侵凌其爲殘酷也尤深切欲剪除而未遂豈謂云云曲軫中霄之念俯憐下國之灾遽遣官軍旋摧賊陣致群兇之顯戮與兆姓以同歡臣敢不載殫向上之誠歸美以報仰答叵涯之惠永矢不諼
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 謝表
  author: 李仁老
  language: lzh
  text: 內宣詔命。外暢威靈。恩實出於非常。涕難禁於增感。伏念臣猥將蕞品。介在荒隅。早襲箕封。謬傳家而負荷。忽遭丹寇。擅入京以侵凌。其爲殘酷也尤深。切欲剪除而未遂。豈謂云云。曲軫中霄之念。俯憐下國之灾。遽遣官軍。旋摧賊陣。致群兇之顯戮。與兆姓以同歡。臣敢不載殫向上之誠。歸美以報。仰答叵涯之惠。永矢不諼。
korean:
  title: 사표
  author: 이인로
  language: kor
  text: 안에서 조명(詔命)을 발하시어 밖으로 위령(威靈)을 선포하옵시니, 은혜가 실로 비상하옵신지라, 감격된 눈물을 금할 수 없나이다.엎드려 생각하옵건대, 신이 외람되게도 조그만 자질로써 먼 구석에 끼어 살면서, 일찍 기봉(箕封)을 계승하여 외람되이 가업(家業)을 이어 지켜왔사온대, 갑자기 글안의 오랑캐가 방자히 서울에 들어와 침노함을 만났습니다. 그의 잔혹함이 극심하여 기어이 전제(剪除)하려 하였으나 이루지 못하였는데, 뜻밖에도 운운. 중소(中宵 밤중)의 진념(軫念)을 특별히 베푸시고 굽어 하국(下國)의 재난을 불쌍히 여기시어 얼른 관군(官軍)을 보내어 금방 적진(賊陣)을 격멸하여 군흉(群兇)을 모조리 주륙(誅戮)하게 하시오니, 만 백성이 모두 기뻐하옵나이다.신이 감히 위로 향하는 충성을 다하여 보답하지 않사오리이까. 우러러 가없는 은혜를 갚고자 길이 잊지 않기를 맹세하옵나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0390_010_0140&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Memorial of Gratitude
  author: Lee In-ro
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your majesty issues commands within the court and displays divine authority without—such grace transcends the ordinary, and tears of gratitude cannot be restrained.

    I humbly reflect: though I am unworthy, a man of modest station dwelling in remote obscurity, I inherited my family's modest fief in my youth and took up the burden of ancestral duty. Yet suddenly the savage raiders breached our capital with their cruel depredations—their viciousness knew no bounds, and though I longed to strike them down, I could not succeed. And yet, unexpectedly...

    Your majesty, in the watches of the night, harbored tender concern for us. Taking pity on our distant realm's calamity, you swiftly dispatched your armies, and in a flash the enemy ranks were crushed. The rebel chiefs met their just execution, and all the common people rejoiced together.

    How dare I fail to offer my utmost devotion in return? I bow low to repay your boundless grace, and I pledge eternal remembrance of this mercy.
  footnotes:
    - A memorial of thanks, likely written after royal forces aided in suppressing a rebellion or invasion that threatened the author's region.
    - The 'savage raiders' (丹寇) likely refer to a specific historical threat; the Jurchen or Khitan invasions were common during the Goryeo period.
    - '''Boxia fief'' (箕封) is a traditional reference to legitimate hereditary rule, suggesting the author held legitimate regional authority.'
